WEBVTT

1
00:00:49.520 --> 00:00:50.880
[GRUNTING]

2
00:00:52.200 --> 00:01:03.120
Fuck.

3
00:01:03.760 --> 00:01:05.960
Fucking fuck!

4
00:01:06.160 --> 00:01:07.600
Watch it, old man.

5
00:01:15.240 --> 00:01:18.360
What the fuck? You're doing it wrong!

6
00:01:19.360 --> 00:01:21.160
MAN:
Needle is doing what the needle does.

7
00:01:21.320 --> 00:01:22.320
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

8
00:01:22.480 --> 00:01:24.240
What the fuck is that supposed to mean?

9
00:01:24.400 --> 00:01:26.320
The irezumi does not hide the skin.

10
00:01:26.720 --> 00:01:28.960
The tattoo reveals
the nature of the man...

11
00:01:29.120 --> 00:01:32.880
...and illuminates the four noble
professions in The Book of Five Rings:

12
00:01:33.360 --> 00:01:37.040
The warrior, the artist, the merchant
and the farmer.

13
00:01:37.200 --> 00:01:39.560
If there is a conflict
between the needle and the skin...

14
00:01:39.720 --> 00:01:42.240
...between the mark and the man...

15
00:01:42.400 --> 00:01:46.400
...then perhaps the path you've chosen
is not the path for which you're suited.

16
00:01:47.960 --> 00:01:49.480
What did you just say, old man?

17
00:01:49.680 --> 00:01:50.760
Huh?

18
00:01:51.400 --> 00:01:53.520
I know you didn't just disrespect me,
did you?

19
00:01:53.800 --> 00:01:55.520
You that fucking stupid?

20
00:01:55.680 --> 00:01:58.960
You disrespect me and I'll tattoo
the ceiling with your fucking brains.

21
00:02:02.360 --> 00:02:04.080
No disrespect.

22
00:02:05.240 --> 00:02:06.880
You're lucky.

23
00:02:07.040 --> 00:02:10.760
I can't kill you
until you finish this thing. Bang.

24
00:02:11.760 --> 00:02:13.200
Give me that mirror.

25
00:02:13.360 --> 00:02:15.280
Let's see how it's looking.

26
00:02:15.440 --> 00:02:16.920
Not bad, not bad.

27
00:02:17.080 --> 00:02:18.960
YAKUZA:
Hey, boss. This just came for you.

28
00:02:19.120 --> 00:02:21.400
- What is it?
- A letter.

29
00:02:21.840 --> 00:02:23.200
So open it, dumbass.

30
00:02:27.680 --> 00:02:29.120
What?

31
00:02:29.280 --> 00:02:32.440
- What is it?
YAKUZA: It looks like sand.

32
00:02:33.880 --> 00:02:36.000
Yep. Sand.

33
00:02:36.320 --> 00:02:38.240
- Black sand.
- No.

34
00:02:41.320 --> 00:02:42.360
You know what this is?

35
00:02:43.880 --> 00:02:45.320
You wanna let us in on the joke?

36
00:02:45.760 --> 00:02:49.840
Years ago I watched a man
open an envelope like that one.

37
00:02:50.440 --> 00:02:52.080
There were many with him.

38
00:02:52.400 --> 00:02:56.040
And they laughed as you laugh now.

39
00:02:56.720 --> 00:02:59.840
And then it came from the shadows...

40
00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:03.200
...and their laughter
was drowned in blood.

41
00:03:05.520 --> 00:03:07.920
What came out of the shadows?

42
00:03:08.320 --> 00:03:09.840
I cannot say the word.

43
00:03:10.320 --> 00:03:11.760
What word?

44
00:03:14.720 --> 00:03:16.720
That night...

45
00:03:17.040 --> 00:03:19.640
...one of their blades struck here.

46
00:03:19.800 --> 00:03:22.560
I should have died
but for an accident of birth.

47
00:03:22.720 --> 00:03:27.400
My heart is here, on the other side.

48
00:03:29.680 --> 00:03:31.600
The fuck is that?

49
00:03:31.920 --> 00:03:34.160
It looks like a ninja, boss.

50
00:03:35.320 --> 00:03:36.680
A ninja?

51
00:03:36.840 --> 00:03:40.640
Are you kidding me? That's the word
you're afraid to say? Ninja?

52
00:03:41.480 --> 00:03:44.560
Ninja, ninja, ninja.
Yeah, you old fuck.

53
00:03:44.720 --> 00:03:45.720
[ALL LAUGHING]

54
00:03:45.880 --> 00:03:47.200
Yeah, you had me going.

55
00:03:47.600 --> 00:03:51.760
- Ninja. That's some good shit.
YAKUZA: Ninja.

56
00:03:51.920 --> 00:03:54.880
[ALL LAUGHING]

57
00:04:02.080 --> 00:04:03.840
[WOMEN SCREAMING]

58
00:04:14.240 --> 00:04:15.920
Wanna fuck with me, huh?

59
00:04:19.040 --> 00:04:20.520
Wanna fuck with me?

60
00:04:21.520 --> 00:04:22.920
[YAKUZA SCREAMING]

61
00:04:26.800 --> 00:04:27.760
[SCREAMS]

62
00:05:02.680 --> 00:05:06.200
Look, you don't have to do this.

63
00:05:06.640 --> 00:05:09.720
Whatever they're paying you,
I'll double it.

64
00:05:09.880 --> 00:05:11.120
I'll triple it.

65
00:05:11.520 --> 00:05:12.720
You hear me?

66
00:05:13.080 --> 00:05:14.640
I'll pay you whatever you want.

67
00:05:14.800 --> 00:05:17.200
You cannot bargain with it,
you cannot reason with it...

68
00:05:17.360 --> 00:05:20.360
...because it is not a human being.

69
00:05:20.520 --> 00:05:23.280
It is a demon sent straight from hell.

70
00:05:23.440 --> 00:05:25.000
You shut your face, old man!

71
00:05:25.160 --> 00:05:27.000
I'll blow your fuck...

72
00:05:47.080 --> 00:05:50.360
MAN:
For 57 years, I've told your story.

73
00:05:50.520 --> 00:05:55.760
No one ever believed me,
but you are real, aren't you?

74
00:06:14.000 --> 00:06:15.760
Is all that for the Delgata case?

75
00:06:17.400 --> 00:06:18.560
This is Delgata.

76
00:06:19.520 --> 00:06:21.000
- And the rest?
- Evidence.

77
00:06:21.280 --> 00:06:22.640
For?

78
00:06:22.960 --> 00:06:24.760
Oh, no, not again, Mika, please.

79
00:06:24.920 --> 00:06:27.360
What is the problem?
You've trusted my research before.

80
00:06:27.520 --> 00:06:30.360
Here's a question. Which of these
does not belong in this sentence:

81
00:06:30.520 --> 00:06:34.280
Laptop, space shuttle,
nanotechnology, ninja.

82
00:06:35.240 --> 00:06:37.920
All I'm asking for is an hour.
That's all.

83
00:06:40.080 --> 00:06:42.560
Why do I think I'm gonna regret this?

84
00:06:43.080 --> 00:06:44.360
MIKA:
Remember the Eulmi Incident?

85
00:06:44.520 --> 00:06:47.280
Korean queen, late 1800s,
killed by one of these ninja clans.

86
00:06:47.440 --> 00:06:49.240
Ozunu, I think.

87
00:06:49.400 --> 00:06:52.920
Now, I've been going through
the original transcripts of the trial...

88
00:06:53.080 --> 00:06:54.240
...of Kunitomo Shigeaki.

89
00:06:54.720 --> 00:06:59.040
The prosecutor questioned Shigeaki
about a payment of 100 pounds of gold.

90
00:06:59.200 --> 00:07:02.400
Shigeaki answered that he didn't know
what the prosecutor was talking about.

91
00:07:02.560 --> 00:07:04.240
The question
was never brought up again.

92
00:07:04.400 --> 00:07:06.760
But what pinged for me was the amount.

93
00:07:06.920 --> 00:07:09.880
The exact same amount rumored
to have been paid to the Ozunu Clan...

94
00:07:10.040 --> 00:07:13.280
...for the yakuza massacre that happened
last week in Osaka.

95
00:07:13.440 --> 00:07:15.360
So you wonder,
in this ever-changing world...

96
00:07:15.520 --> 00:07:17.520
...if the cost of a man's life
remains the same.

97
00:07:17.680 --> 00:07:21.360
Exactly. I mean, I figure these clans
are like, what, a thousand years old?

98
00:07:21.520 --> 00:07:22.800
They probably don't change.

99
00:07:23.280 --> 00:07:26.840
So I started looking at
international wire transfers...

100
00:07:27.000 --> 00:07:31.240
...targeting banks in the regions
of several high-profile assassinations.

101
00:07:31.520 --> 00:07:33.680
And bingo.
Russian Prime Minister Zhukov.

102
00:07:34.000 --> 00:07:35.840
The day before the assassination...

103
00:07:36.000 --> 00:07:40.720
...$1,555,999 and 90 cents...

104
00:07:40.880 --> 00:07:43.360
...was transferred
from the Bank of Shanghai.

105
00:07:43.760 --> 00:07:46.920
That is the exact market equivalent
of 100 pounds of gold.

106
00:07:48.720 --> 00:07:52.120
- Okay, you got me, this is interesting.
- The clans are real, Ryan.

107
00:07:52.280 --> 00:07:55.320
They steal children
and turn them into assassins.

108
00:07:55.480 --> 00:07:57.760
Look, Mika, no one's denying
the historical facts...

109
00:07:57.920 --> 00:08:00.240
...but this thing doesn't make sense
in a modern world.

110
00:08:00.400 --> 00:08:03.720
They're real. You can call them spooks
or assassins or whatever you want...

111
00:08:03.880 --> 00:08:07.920
...if it makes you feel better, but they are
out there and they are killing people.

112
00:08:08.080 --> 00:08:10.160
And nobody is doing a damn thing
to stop them.

113
00:08:17.680 --> 00:08:19.360
Hi. Excuse me.

114
00:08:19.880 --> 00:08:20.880
Would you mind?

115
00:08:21.800 --> 00:08:24.400
If it's not too much trouble,
could you help me with this?

116
00:08:39.920 --> 00:08:41.440
What clan are you from?

117
00:08:43.040 --> 00:08:44.560
What are you doing in Berlin?

118
00:08:44.720 --> 00:08:46.080
I don't understand.

119
00:08:51.760 --> 00:08:55.120
[BOTH SHOUTING AND GRUNTING]

120
00:09:00.240 --> 00:09:02.800
[INDISTINCT DIALOGUE ON TV]

121
00:09:03.760 --> 00:09:05.120
[WOMAN SCREAMS ON TV]

122
00:09:07.680 --> 00:09:09.360
What is going on?

123
00:09:09.800 --> 00:09:11.440
[WASHING MACHINE CLANGING]

124
00:09:24.440 --> 00:09:25.520
MIKA:
You found something?

125
00:09:25.680 --> 00:09:29.040
MASLOW: I was digging around trying to see
what I could come up with and I found this.

126
00:09:29.200 --> 00:09:31.600
A report. A friend of mine in Moscow
tipped me to it.

127
00:09:31.920 --> 00:09:33.560
It was written during the Cold War...

128
00:09:33.720 --> 00:09:37.240
...by a high-ranking KGB agent
named Alexi Sabatin.

129
00:09:37.400 --> 00:09:40.520
He raises the possibility that
a number of political assassinations...

130
00:09:40.680 --> 00:09:43.280
...were conducted by an ancient
but sophisticated network...

131
00:09:43.440 --> 00:09:45.840
...he calls the Nine Clans.

132
00:09:46.480 --> 00:09:49.800
- Mind you, he doesn't call them ninjas.
- What happened to him?

133
00:09:49.960 --> 00:09:52.560
Same thing that's gonna happen to me
if I hang around with you.

134
00:09:53.560 --> 00:09:56.000
Kicked out of the service
for mental instability.

135
00:09:57.280 --> 00:09:58.600
You believe it now, don't you?

136
00:09:59.760 --> 00:10:01.400
Ninjas.

137
00:10:01.840 --> 00:10:04.560
- You gotta be joking.
- Well, then why are you doing all this?

138
00:10:05.520 --> 00:10:06.480
I don't know.

139
00:10:06.640 --> 00:10:09.280
But I can guarantee you
it has nothing to do with the fact...

140
00:10:09.440 --> 00:10:12.520
...that you're the most attractive
researcher I have ever worked with.

141
00:10:24.240 --> 00:10:25.360
Oh, Mr. Nan.

142
00:10:25.520 --> 00:10:26.720
Good, you are back.

143
00:10:26.880 --> 00:10:30.160
We had a heating problem,
and I had to go into your apartment.

144
00:10:31.600 --> 00:10:34.360
- Is it all right?
- It's all fixed.

145
00:10:34.520 --> 00:10:36.760
You keep it very dark and spare in there.

146
00:10:36.920 --> 00:10:40.080
And forgive me, but I couldn't help
noticing your suitcases.

147
00:10:42.680 --> 00:10:45.200
RAIZO: I told you,
my father was a very sick man.

148
00:10:45.360 --> 00:10:46.960
LANDLADY:
Do you have to leave Berlin soon?

149
00:10:47.120 --> 00:10:49.760
RAIZO:
Not yet, but I am expecting a phone call.

150
00:10:49.920 --> 00:10:51.920
LANDLADY:
I'm sorry to hear that.

151
00:10:52.080 --> 00:10:56.040
RAIZO:
One day, death will come for us all.

152
00:11:06.600 --> 00:11:12.640
[OZUNU SPEAKS IN JAPANESE]

153
00:11:13.600 --> 00:11:15.720
OZUNU:
Wherever you are...

154
00:11:16.520 --> 00:11:19.080
...wherever you may go...

155
00:11:22.640 --> 00:11:26.440
...you must never forget who you are...

156
00:11:26.720 --> 00:11:29.240
...how you came to be.

157
00:11:29.600 --> 00:11:31.720
You are Ozunu.

158
00:11:32.600 --> 00:11:34.480
You are part of me...

159
00:11:35.040 --> 00:11:37.000
...as I am part of you.

160
00:11:37.320 --> 00:11:40.560
This is the truth of your lives...

161
00:11:40.720 --> 00:11:44.040
...and it will remain true after death.

162
00:11:46.000 --> 00:11:47.920
This is my new son.

163
00:11:48.600 --> 00:11:52.000
I have given him the name Raizo.

164
00:11:52.480 --> 00:11:54.880
Welcome him as your brother.

165
00:11:55.120 --> 00:11:57.400
ALL:
Welcome, Raizo.

166
00:12:00.040 --> 00:12:01.480
[KETTLE WHISTLES]

167
00:12:17.520 --> 00:12:20.240
OZUNU:
The body must obey the will.

168
00:12:20.400 --> 00:12:22.120
Hunger and thirst...

169
00:12:22.280 --> 00:12:26.280
...even the blood in your veins,
are the body's weakness.

170
00:12:34.040 --> 00:12:35.240
Master them...

171
00:12:37.000 --> 00:12:39.480
...and you master the self.

172
00:12:40.440 --> 00:12:43.280
[SPEAKING IN JAPANESE]

173
00:12:45.400 --> 00:12:49.200
This is the power of the Ozunu Clan.

174
00:12:49.360 --> 00:12:51.920
This is the way of the ninja.

175
00:12:52.800 --> 00:12:57.520
Eat tonight and you work
twice as hard tomorrow.

176
00:13:06.280 --> 00:13:08.560
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

177
00:13:22.560 --> 00:13:24.600
OZUNU:
What is the lesson?

178
00:13:26.000 --> 00:13:27.280
Look at your brother.

179
00:13:28.120 --> 00:13:29.680
Life is combat.

180
00:13:30.640 --> 00:13:32.560
You know this truth.

181
00:13:33.080 --> 00:13:35.440
Abandoned by your parents...

182
00:13:35.760 --> 00:13:39.120
...without a home,
without people to care for you...

183
00:13:39.440 --> 00:13:41.600
...you should have died.

184
00:13:41.760 --> 00:13:43.600
But instead you fought.

185
00:13:44.240 --> 00:13:48.160
As you did here today,
you fought and you won.

186
00:13:48.480 --> 00:13:53.760
In combat, you face the enemy
without doubt, without pity or remorse.

187
00:13:53.920 --> 00:13:57.360
To survive, you must learn
to fear nothing at all.

188
00:14:23.440 --> 00:14:26.560
OZUNU:
Pain breeds weakness.

189
00:14:30.240 --> 00:14:33.040
Remember, suffering exists...

190
00:14:33.680 --> 00:14:36.880
...only because weakness exists.

191
00:14:48.680 --> 00:14:50.120
[SQUEAKING]

192
00:14:55.760 --> 00:14:57.360
You must hate all weakness.

193
00:14:57.520 --> 00:15:01.320
Hate it in others,
but most of all, hate it in yourself.

194
00:15:36.120 --> 00:15:38.480
[GRUNTING SOFTLY]

195
00:15:51.600 --> 00:15:53.040
[RAIZO GRUNTS]

196
00:16:29.120 --> 00:16:31.000
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

197
00:16:46.920 --> 00:16:48.000
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

198
00:16:49.680 --> 00:16:51.440
MIKA: Mrs. Sabatin?
- Yeah.

199
00:16:51.600 --> 00:16:54.800
I'm Mika Coretti with Europol.
We spoke on the phone.

200
00:16:57.840 --> 00:17:00.040
You said you read
my husband's report, yes?

201
00:17:00.200 --> 00:17:01.200
Yes.

202
00:17:02.240 --> 00:17:06.120
I understand the report caused some
problems for him within the KGB.

203
00:17:06.280 --> 00:17:09.280
The report caused problems
for Alexi's career...

204
00:17:09.440 --> 00:17:14.040
...the way Moses caused problems
for the Pharaoh. Very unpleasant.

205
00:17:14.200 --> 00:17:15.280
What happened?

206
00:17:15.440 --> 00:17:17.520
About two years ago...

207
00:17:17.680 --> 00:17:20.080
...after the assassination of Zhukov...

208
00:17:20.240 --> 00:17:23.440
...the report drew attention.

209
00:17:23.640 --> 00:17:25.320
After that...

210
00:17:25.480 --> 00:17:26.760
...everything was different.

211
00:17:27.840 --> 00:17:32.680
Alexi hired men to change all the locks
and put in more of them.

212
00:17:32.840 --> 00:17:35.520
Locks on the windows,
locks on the doors, locks on the locks.

213
00:17:35.680 --> 00:17:38.000
He put in cameras and motion sensors...

214
00:17:38.160 --> 00:17:41.440
...and lights. Everywhere, lights.

215
00:17:41.800 --> 00:17:44.560
"There can be no shadows," he said.

216
00:17:46.160 --> 00:17:47.240
"No shadows."

217
00:17:49.120 --> 00:17:51.600
Then one day, a man came to the door.

218
00:17:51.760 --> 00:17:54.760
They talked in Alexi's study
for some time, and then...

219
00:17:55.560 --> 00:17:57.560
...the young man left.

220
00:17:58.400 --> 00:18:00.400
My husband was a soldier.

221
00:18:00.560 --> 00:18:03.240
Member of Russian intelligence.

222
00:18:03.440 --> 00:18:05.480
He was not a man to frighten easily.

223
00:18:06.000 --> 00:18:10.800
But when I came to the door,
in his eyes I saw fear.

224
00:18:10.960 --> 00:18:13.360
And then he stood up...

225
00:18:13.520 --> 00:18:17.520
...he kissed me and told me
that he loved me very much.

226
00:18:17.680 --> 00:18:19.360
[SPEAKING IN RUSSIAN]

227
00:18:19.720 --> 00:18:21.360
He said...

228
00:18:23.280 --> 00:18:26.000
...I should always remember that.

229
00:18:27.840 --> 00:18:29.520
Do you know what they talked about?

230
00:18:29.680 --> 00:18:33.320
No. He said it was safer that way.

231
00:18:34.600 --> 00:18:36.160
Can I ask how he died?

232
00:18:38.720 --> 00:18:40.840
The lights went out.

233
00:18:41.000 --> 00:18:42.400
[ALARM RINGING]

234
00:18:46.600 --> 00:18:51.240
You are the first person who has
taken my husband's work seriously.

235
00:18:52.720 --> 00:18:56.720
It would be good to know
that he did not die without cause.

236
00:19:06.320 --> 00:19:08.360
He would want you to have this.

237
00:20:01.760 --> 00:20:03.520
MIKA:
Who are you?

238
00:20:36.800 --> 00:20:38.000
Hiyah!

239
00:21:55.160 --> 00:21:56.880
Did Takeshi's blow hurt you?

240
00:21:57.560 --> 00:21:59.280
You think this is pain.

241
00:21:59.800 --> 00:22:01.040
You are mistaken.

242
00:22:05.680 --> 00:22:07.280
[GRUNTING]

243
00:22:15.040 --> 00:22:17.360
[RAIZO SCREAMING]

244
00:22:17.600 --> 00:22:19.760
That is true pain.

245
00:22:19.920 --> 00:22:20.920
[SCREAMING]

246
00:22:21.080 --> 00:22:22.480
Here is your test, Raizo.

247
00:22:22.920 --> 00:22:24.240
Survive the night.

248
00:22:30.120 --> 00:22:32.600
[RAIZO SCREAMING]

249
00:22:37.600 --> 00:22:39.240
[SCREAMING]

250
00:22:54.800 --> 00:22:57.200
[GRUNTING AND PANTING]

251
00:23:22.800 --> 00:23:24.720
Very good, Raizo.

252
00:23:25.200 --> 00:23:26.760
Very good.

253
00:23:36.800 --> 00:23:40.360
Boy, you're like a dog with a bone
on that computer, aren't you?

254
00:23:40.520 --> 00:23:41.520
Excuse me?

255
00:23:42.280 --> 00:23:43.760
Agent Zabranski...

256
00:23:43.960 --> 00:23:45.840
...lnternal Affairs.

257
00:23:46.000 --> 00:23:48.400
Need to ask you a couple of questions.

258
00:23:49.040 --> 00:23:51.480
- You're Mika Coretti, yeah?
- Mm-hm.

259
00:23:51.640 --> 00:23:53.880
Forensic researcher.

260
00:23:54.040 --> 00:23:56.320
You work a lot with Agent Maslow,
that right?

261
00:23:56.720 --> 00:23:58.560
A few cases, yeah.

262
00:23:58.720 --> 00:24:01.360
You have something
of a social relationship.

263
00:24:01.520 --> 00:24:04.880
- Excuse me?
- You had lunch with him on the 13th...

264
00:24:05.280 --> 00:24:06.960
...and again on the 18th.

265
00:24:07.360 --> 00:24:08.400
How do you know that?

266
00:24:09.560 --> 00:24:12.000
- Isn't it true?
- I'm not sure.

267
00:24:12.160 --> 00:24:16.320
We do have lunch together sometimes,
but that's usually when we're working.

268
00:24:16.480 --> 00:24:19.840
Has Agent Maslow seemed different
to you lately in any way?

269
00:24:20.000 --> 00:24:23.440
I mean, has he said or done anything
that struck you as unusual?

270
00:24:23.600 --> 00:24:26.000
No. Why?

271
00:24:26.400 --> 00:24:28.120
Has Agent Maslow done something?

272
00:24:29.040 --> 00:24:30.720
Just routine.

273
00:24:30.880 --> 00:24:33.520
The agency cares about
its field operatives.

274
00:24:33.680 --> 00:24:37.120
We monitor for signs of stress, fatigue...

275
00:24:37.280 --> 00:24:38.560
...mental exhaustion.

276
00:24:39.640 --> 00:24:41.920
Agent Maslow has a serious caseload.

277
00:24:44.720 --> 00:24:47.880
That much work can wear on a man.

278
00:24:52.000 --> 00:24:55.200
MIKA: Zabranski came to my office.
MASLOW: Yeah, I got a surprise visit too.

279
00:24:55.360 --> 00:24:57.680
MIKA: He made it real clear, Ryan.
They're watching us.

280
00:25:00.160 --> 00:25:03.600
I don't get the full picture quite yet,
but I know a warning when I see one.

281
00:25:03.760 --> 00:25:06.520
- But why?
- Why? It's obvious.

282
00:25:06.680 --> 00:25:09.480
If this little fantasy of yours
has any chance of being real...

283
00:25:09.640 --> 00:25:13.240
...then these clans are gonna have
some pretty majorjuice protecting them.

284
00:25:13.400 --> 00:25:15.040
So, what are you gonna do?

285
00:25:15.320 --> 00:25:19.120
We are gonna tiptoe very carefully
from here on in, you understand?

286
00:25:19.280 --> 00:25:21.640
You do nothing without
checking with me first.

287
00:25:22.160 --> 00:25:24.760
- Got it?
- Got it.

288
00:25:24.920 --> 00:25:25.920
[CAMERA CLICKS]

289
00:25:46.480 --> 00:25:51.080
ALEXl: A 14th-century scroll refers to
one of the oldest of the Nine Clans...

290
00:25:51.360 --> 00:25:53.320
...as the Clan of Black Sand.

291
00:25:54.720 --> 00:25:58.960
The Islamic explorer lbn Battuta
journeyed with a group of orphans...

292
00:25:59.120 --> 00:26:01.760
...that were being taken
to a remote shido...

293
00:26:01.920 --> 00:26:04.240
...hidden among snowcapped mountains.

294
00:26:04.800 --> 00:26:07.520
Battuta describes a ceremonial dinner...

295
00:26:07.680 --> 00:26:10.400
...followed by a display of martial skill.

296
00:26:10.560 --> 00:26:14.560
The combatants were children,
neither beyond the age of 10.

297
00:26:15.480 --> 00:26:19.920
His hosts explained that a man's life
must be made meaningless...

298
00:26:20.080 --> 00:26:22.120
...compared to the life of the clan.

299
00:26:22.280 --> 00:26:24.480
Own the meaning of a man's life...

300
00:26:24.640 --> 00:26:26.960
...and you own his heart.

301
00:26:34.000 --> 00:26:38.440
[THUMPING]

302
00:26:56.600 --> 00:27:00.920
You shouldn't do that. It's against
the rules. If they catch you...

303
00:27:01.080 --> 00:27:03.680
- Then they catch me.
- They'll put you in the box.

304
00:27:04.640 --> 00:27:08.560
I believe the heart of the tree
knows which way it needs to grow.

305
00:27:10.240 --> 00:27:13.640
- Trees don't have hearts.
- Everything has a heart.

306
00:27:15.000 --> 00:27:16.880
I don't.

307
00:27:17.440 --> 00:27:18.480
Really?

308
00:27:19.240 --> 00:27:20.320
Let me see.

309
00:27:24.960 --> 00:27:25.960
Hello?

310
00:27:26.120 --> 00:27:28.400
[HEART BEATING FAINTLY]

311
00:27:30.200 --> 00:27:31.600
It's saying hello back...

312
00:27:31.760 --> 00:27:35.280
...and that it's happy to meet me,
but it misses you.

313
00:27:36.680 --> 00:27:39.120
- Liar.
- I'm not lying.

314
00:27:39.600 --> 00:27:41.640
Listen to mine.

315
00:27:49.520 --> 00:27:51.440
[HEART BEATING]

316
00:28:26.880 --> 00:28:31.320
OZUNU: For an entire year, you shall live
without one of your senses...

317
00:28:31.480 --> 00:28:35.120
...beginning with the sense
you rely on the most.

318
00:28:54.160 --> 00:28:56.880
You must see with more than your eyes.

319
00:28:57.080 --> 00:29:01.320
[SWORD SWOOSHING]

320
00:29:01.480 --> 00:29:02.840
[FOOTSTEPS]

321
00:29:11.720 --> 00:29:14.640
[SWORD SWOOSHING]

322
00:30:37.680 --> 00:30:45.640
[HEART BEATING]

323
00:30:49.280 --> 00:30:52.480
[HEARTS BEATING IN UNISON]

324
00:31:07.040 --> 00:31:08.240
[GRUNTS]

325
00:31:13.320 --> 00:31:15.520
Cut him, Kiriko.

326
00:31:15.680 --> 00:31:18.320
All failure must be sown into the flesh.

327
00:31:20.080 --> 00:31:21.440
Cut him.

328
00:31:38.640 --> 00:31:39.720
You know the law.

329
00:32:53.840 --> 00:32:55.880
I told you.

330
00:32:56.440 --> 00:32:58.160
I tried to warn you.

331
00:32:59.040 --> 00:33:00.760
Yes.

332
00:33:01.440 --> 00:33:03.280
You did.

333
00:33:03.760 --> 00:33:05.320
Why, Kiriko?

334
00:33:06.920 --> 00:33:08.560
Why?

335
00:33:11.440 --> 00:33:13.520
Why am I in here...

336
00:33:14.400 --> 00:33:17.160
...or why are you out there?

337
00:33:40.080 --> 00:33:54.920
[THUNDER CRACKING]

338
00:34:09.800 --> 00:34:11.440
RAIZO:
Kiriko!

339
00:34:12.320 --> 00:34:13.680
Why are you doing this?

340
00:34:15.160 --> 00:34:16.160
I have to.

341
00:34:17.200 --> 00:34:20.560
You know the law.
He will cut your heart from your chest.

342
00:34:21.840 --> 00:34:23.400
No.

343
00:34:23.920 --> 00:34:25.480
He can never touch my heart.

344
00:34:33.440 --> 00:34:35.360
[HEART BEATING]

345
00:34:45.440 --> 00:34:46.640
Come with me.

346
00:34:47.320 --> 00:34:49.800
Where? What is out there?

347
00:34:50.520 --> 00:34:52.000
Life.

348
00:34:56.720 --> 00:34:59.000
My life is here.

349
00:35:33.960 --> 00:35:35.600
[PHONE RINGING]

350
00:35:38.160 --> 00:35:40.440
[WOMAN SPEAKS IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE
ON PHONE AND HANGS UP]

351
00:35:56.320 --> 00:35:57.800
[CAR ALARM CHIRPS]

352
00:36:00.160 --> 00:36:01.160
MASLOW:
Shh.

353
00:36:01.320 --> 00:36:02.920
Fucking Christ, Ryan.

354
00:36:03.080 --> 00:36:07.280
I'm sorry I couldn't talk earlier, Mika.
They're watching me. Get in.

355
00:36:14.720 --> 00:36:16.840
Where have you been?
I've been calling your office.

356
00:36:17.000 --> 00:36:18.600
Now I know how Sabatin must have felt.

357
00:36:18.960 --> 00:36:20.000
What's happened?

358
00:36:20.160 --> 00:36:22.840
MASLOW: Right now I've got
Internal Affairs, Homeland Security...

359
00:36:23.040 --> 00:36:25.840
...the CIA and for all I know
the Martian military in my office...

360
00:36:26.000 --> 00:36:27.360
...tearing the place apart.

361
00:36:28.480 --> 00:36:29.480
What are we gonna do?

362
00:36:29.640 --> 00:36:31.760
You are gonna pack your bags,
go on holiday.

363
00:36:31.920 --> 00:36:32.880
No way.

364
00:36:33.040 --> 00:36:35.160
Don't argue.
I trusted you, you gotta trust me.

365
00:36:35.320 --> 00:36:37.680
I'm sorry, I can't let you lose
yourjob because of me.

366
00:36:37.840 --> 00:36:40.800
I'm not talking about losing my job.
Take this.

367
00:36:40.960 --> 00:36:43.920
It's clean, untraceable, no serial number.

368
00:36:44.760 --> 00:36:46.960
- Ryan?
- Yeah, I know.

369
00:36:47.120 --> 00:36:51.120
I've investigated world bank organizations,
drug cartels, arms dealers.

370
00:36:51.280 --> 00:36:53.560
I've never faced this kind of heat.

371
00:36:54.080 --> 00:36:56.720
For ninjas. It's fucking unbelievable.

372
00:37:00.200 --> 00:37:01.760
MIKA:
Excuse me.

373
00:37:03.200 --> 00:37:05.200
- Hey.
MAN: Hi.

374
00:37:05.360 --> 00:37:07.280
So, what's going on?

375
00:37:07.600 --> 00:37:12.560
Power's out. Us, the building behind us,
and that one across the street.

376
00:37:12.720 --> 00:37:15.440
It seems like every few months,
boom, the light's out.

377
00:37:17.200 --> 00:37:18.680
Okay.

378
00:37:19.120 --> 00:37:20.640
Thanks.

379
00:37:46.040 --> 00:37:47.480
[CLANGING]

380
00:38:32.800 --> 00:38:34.800
[GUNSHOTS]

381
00:39:01.240 --> 00:39:02.320
MIKA:
Ah!

382
00:39:22.440 --> 00:39:24.280
[PANTING]

383
00:39:32.920 --> 00:39:34.960
RAIZO: More will come.
- What?

384
00:39:35.120 --> 00:39:36.920
They won't stop until you're dead.

385
00:39:37.080 --> 00:39:38.800
MIKA:
Oh, God.

386
00:39:39.720 --> 00:39:41.040
RAIZO:
A gun won't help you.

387
00:39:41.200 --> 00:39:43.200
MIKA: Well, I don't have
a lot of options, okay?

388
00:39:43.360 --> 00:39:44.600
I once took a Tae Bo class...

389
00:39:44.760 --> 00:39:47.600
...but that is the extent
of my kung-fu abilities, all right?

390
00:39:47.760 --> 00:39:51.080
I can help you, but you have to trust me.

391
00:39:55.640 --> 00:39:57.400
MIKA:
Okay.

392
00:40:12.920 --> 00:40:14.000
Do you know me?

393
00:40:16.520 --> 00:40:18.040
How?

394
00:40:20.040 --> 00:40:24.080
Security camera in New York
recorded you fighting one of them.

395
00:40:24.240 --> 00:40:25.280
You know about them?

396
00:40:26.480 --> 00:40:27.920
A little.

397
00:40:28.440 --> 00:40:30.560
Well, there are these clans.

398
00:40:31.000 --> 00:40:35.080
And, apparently, they've been
supplying assassins to governments...

399
00:40:35.240 --> 00:40:37.320
...or anyone who has
100 pounds of gold...

400
00:40:37.840 --> 00:40:40.240
...for the last thousand years.

401
00:40:40.840 --> 00:40:42.480
RAIZO:
His name was Jin.

402
00:40:44.400 --> 00:40:46.240
Wait, you knew him?

403
00:40:46.400 --> 00:40:49.520
- He was not born an assassin.
- You're from his clan.

404
00:40:49.680 --> 00:40:50.920
[DOG BARKING]

405
00:40:51.080 --> 00:40:53.160
- They why did you stop him?
- They're coming.

406
00:40:54.000 --> 00:40:55.440
Who?

407
00:41:02.160 --> 00:41:06.480
NINJA 1 [WHISPERING]:
It was him, the traitor, Raizo. Murderer.

408
00:41:07.800 --> 00:41:10.800
- Fresh kill.
NINJA 2: He's with the girl.

409
00:41:10.960 --> 00:41:12.240
Still close.

410
00:41:12.400 --> 00:41:14.720
Very close.

411
00:41:19.320 --> 00:41:22.120
TAKESHl:
Run, little brother, run.

412
00:41:23.880 --> 00:41:26.640
OZUNU:
Weakness compels strength.

413
00:41:26.800 --> 00:41:29.200
Betrayal begets blood.

414
00:41:29.360 --> 00:41:31.680
This is the law of the Nine Clans.

415
00:41:31.840 --> 00:41:32.840
Ah!

416
00:41:33.000 --> 00:41:34.240
[THUNDER CRACKING]

417
00:41:34.400 --> 00:41:42.000
[KIRIKO SCREAMING]

418
00:42:00.800 --> 00:42:02.640
OZUNU:
We have been betrayed.

419
00:42:02.800 --> 00:42:06.960
A child of mine, my daughter,
betrayed us.

420
00:42:07.120 --> 00:42:11.960
She refused my gifts, rejected our clan.

421
00:42:12.880 --> 00:42:16.720
Her shame can only be purged
with blood.

422
00:42:17.120 --> 00:42:18.640
You.

423
00:42:22.720 --> 00:42:26.760
You, my son, who returned her
shall have this honor.

424
00:42:56.200 --> 00:42:57.720
Ah!

425
00:43:11.120 --> 00:43:14.080
- Where are we going?
- Doesn't matter.

426
00:43:15.440 --> 00:43:17.360
You think they're following us?

427
00:43:17.520 --> 00:43:19.080
I know they're following us.

428
00:43:19.240 --> 00:43:21.520
MIKA:
I don't see anything back there.

429
00:43:21.880 --> 00:43:23.600
They have our scent.

430
00:43:23.760 --> 00:43:25.960
Following our scent? Like dogs?

431
00:43:26.120 --> 00:43:28.680
No. Like wolves.

432
00:43:31.760 --> 00:43:33.120
My name's Mika, by the way.

433
00:43:35.920 --> 00:43:38.920
Raizo is the name I was given.

434
00:43:39.840 --> 00:43:41.040
So you're an orphan?

435
00:43:44.280 --> 00:43:48.360
If it's okay with you, I'm gonna try
and fill in some of the blanks here.

436
00:43:48.920 --> 00:43:53.520
So you must have been taken by
the Ozunu Clan, trained to be an assassin...

437
00:43:53.680 --> 00:43:57.200
...but something happened and you
decided to opt out of the program.

438
00:43:57.360 --> 00:43:59.920
Now, I don't imagine
that went over so well.

439
00:44:00.080 --> 00:44:02.640
Since they're after me
forjust peeking through the keyhole...

440
00:44:02.800 --> 00:44:04.800
...they must be after you
in, like, a major way.

441
00:44:04.960 --> 00:44:08.080
But you're also after them,
which is why you're in Berlin.

442
00:44:08.240 --> 00:44:10.840
Because Sabatin is one of the few people
pursuing the clans...

443
00:44:11.000 --> 00:44:12.880
...which is why they took him out.

444
00:44:14.640 --> 00:44:16.720
But here's a question I can't answer.

445
00:44:18.640 --> 00:44:19.760
Why did you save me?

446
00:44:30.240 --> 00:44:34.120
OZUNU: Your entire life has brought you
to this moment.

447
00:44:34.360 --> 00:44:37.040
Do not fail yourself.

448
00:44:37.640 --> 00:44:39.600
Do not fail your family.

449
00:44:42.080 --> 00:44:44.400
He's wearing a gold watch.

450
00:44:44.920 --> 00:44:46.960
Bring it to me.

451
00:44:57.960 --> 00:44:59.120
[SIGHS]

452
00:44:59.280 --> 00:45:02.000
[HAND DRYER HUMMING]

453
00:45:24.400 --> 00:45:26.160
That kind of tickled.

454
00:45:33.400 --> 00:45:36.400
It's gonna take more than a knitting needle
to fuck me up, boy!

455
00:46:12.720 --> 00:46:15.040
Ah!

456
00:46:21.240 --> 00:46:42.040
[THUNDER CRACKING]

457
00:47:08.440 --> 00:47:09.840
OZUNU:
Keep it.

458
00:47:10.160 --> 00:47:11.600
It will remind you that...

459
00:47:11.760 --> 00:47:15.560
...every moment of your life
is a gift I have given you.

460
00:47:19.120 --> 00:47:21.360
You have made me proud, my son.

461
00:47:22.320 --> 00:47:25.280
Now the time has come
for you to prove...

462
00:47:25.440 --> 00:47:27.880
...you are true Ozunu.

463
00:47:34.440 --> 00:47:36.560
She tried to run from us...

464
00:47:37.480 --> 00:47:39.400
...from our family.

465
00:47:42.760 --> 00:47:46.520
Takeshi caught her
and returned her to us.

466
00:47:47.960 --> 00:47:50.920
Weakness compels strength.

467
00:47:51.280 --> 00:47:53.320
Betrayal begets blood.

468
00:48:03.960 --> 00:48:07.120
This is the law of the Nine Clans.

469
00:48:22.000 --> 00:48:23.800
Hiyah!

470
00:48:27.520 --> 00:48:29.120
Kill him!

471
00:48:53.720 --> 00:48:55.640
[GRUNTING]

472
00:49:11.320 --> 00:49:13.200
[RAIZO SCREAMING]

473
00:49:27.160 --> 00:49:28.360
You need protection.

474
00:49:28.520 --> 00:49:33.160
No. I want Ozunu,
and I need your help to get him.

475
00:49:35.920 --> 00:49:36.880
Exit here.

476
00:49:45.080 --> 00:49:47.840
- You are a size 36?
- What?

477
00:49:48.000 --> 00:49:49.680
No, size 34.

478
00:49:55.040 --> 00:49:56.440
If you leave while I'm gone...

479
00:49:56.920 --> 00:49:58.720
...they'll hunt you and kill you.

480
00:49:58.880 --> 00:50:00.680
Do you understand?

481
00:50:18.960 --> 00:50:19.960
Get undressed.

482
00:50:20.720 --> 00:50:23.520
Shower, but do not use soap.
Do you smoke?

483
00:50:25.680 --> 00:50:26.960
Put your clothes in here.

484
00:50:30.480 --> 00:50:32.160
These jeans are a little tight.

485
00:50:33.320 --> 00:50:35.360
You said 34.

486
00:50:36.360 --> 00:50:41.520
Yeah, well, it's German sizes.
They must run a little small, I guess.

487
00:50:46.360 --> 00:50:49.040
This is for our scent. Right?

488
00:50:50.000 --> 00:50:51.680
Let's go.

489
00:50:52.200 --> 00:50:54.120
[PHONE RINGING]

490
00:50:56.120 --> 00:50:57.320
- Yeah?
MIKA: Ryan, it's me.

491
00:50:57.480 --> 00:51:00.920
- Mika, I've been calling you for hours.
- I know, I'm in a bit of trouble.

492
00:51:01.080 --> 00:51:02.800
You miss jury service, you're in trouble.

493
00:51:02.960 --> 00:51:04.920
You're in the deepest shit
you've ever been in.

494
00:51:05.080 --> 00:51:06.800
At least I'm not down here by myself.

495
00:51:06.960 --> 00:51:09.000
Sabatin's guy from the tape?
Is he with you?

496
00:51:09.160 --> 00:51:10.600
He's on our side, Ryan.

497
00:51:10.760 --> 00:51:13.040
He wants Ozunu,
but he needs the agency's help.

498
00:51:13.360 --> 00:51:15.760
- Be careful, Mika.
- I trust him.

499
00:51:15.920 --> 00:51:19.880
All right, look, I can't make any promises,
but if he cooperates, I'll do what I can.

500
00:51:20.040 --> 00:51:21.840
- Can you meet us?
- Where?

501
00:51:22.600 --> 00:51:23.840
How about the usual?

502
00:51:30.840 --> 00:51:32.320
There he is.

503
00:51:34.360 --> 00:51:37.080
Now, it's all right. He's a good guy.

504
00:51:39.000 --> 00:51:40.600
- Mika, are you okay?
- Yeah.

505
00:51:40.760 --> 00:51:42.360
Thanks to him.

506
00:51:42.920 --> 00:51:45.280
- Why have you done this?
- Done what?

507
00:51:45.600 --> 00:51:46.920
People will die.

508
00:51:47.520 --> 00:51:49.200
- Now!
MIKA: No!

509
00:51:49.600 --> 00:51:51.200
AGENT 1:
Don't move!

510
00:51:53.360 --> 00:51:56.000
[GRUNTING]

